Definition: A legal document that specifies the terms and conditions of a sale of goods or services between a buyer and a seller.
The body of law that governs the legal obligations between parties who enter into contracts.
A legally binding agreement that is enforceable by law.
The body of law that governs the rights and obligations between individuals and entities within a country.
The body of law that governs the conduct of individuals and entities within a society.
A legal document that grants the holder the right to operate a business or engage in a particular activity.
The body of law that governs the legal relationship between employers and employees.
The body of law that governs the legal relationship between landlords and tenants.
The body of law that governs the legal obligations between individuals and entities involved in intellectual property.
A legal proceeding in which one party seeks to recover monetary damages or other relief from another party.
A legal document that grants the holder the exclusive right to use, manufacture, or sell an invention for a certain period of time.
A legal document that provides evidence of ownership of a specific piece of property.
A legal document that grants the holder the right to use or occupy a property owned by another party.
The body of law that governs the legal relationship between spouses.
The body of law that governs the legal relationship between parents and their children.
A legal document that outlines the distribution of a person's assets and liabilities after their death.
The body of law that governs the legal relationship between consumers and businesses.
A legal document that authorizes one person to act on behalf of another person or entity.
The body of law that governs the legal relationship between debtors and creditors.
A legal document that outlines the terms and conditions of a loan agreement between a lender and a borrower.
